This paper is about a system for symbolic event recognition, which involves reasoning about events and their relationships. This falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI), specifically in the subfield of knowledge representation and reasoning. The paper also discusses implementation and performance, which could be relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and databases (cs.DB). The system is designed to handle real-time data streams, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and distributed computing (cs.DC).
